HEADWORD: Rejudge
<hw>Re*judge"</hw> <pr>(r?-j?j")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To judge
again; to reexamine; to review; to call to a new trial and
decision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Rejudge</qex> his acts, and dignify disgrace.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rejuvenate</ent>⟦br⟧
